_hit_comment: This is Jalani. I would say, you definitely gain information about the location of the part based on the position of the circle, which can consciously and unconsciously affect your estimation of depth (which is information that is implied by --but not explicitly stated within-- the picture). It would also be faster to rank the depths of the keypoints instead of doing pairwise comparisons, though this method does give annotators the chance to be self-inconsistent, which could be important information.
